    },
    {
      "keys": ["windmill", "electricity"],
      "content": "The windmill was a great building project — meant to bring electricity to the farm and ease the animals' labour. It was built with enormous effort, then knocked down once (Napoleon blamed Snowball), rebuilt, and damaged again in a battle with humans. Napoleon points to the windmill as proof of the animals' progress under his leadership. In truth the animals worked harder for it and ate no better. Napoleon presents every setback with the windmill as the work of enemies and saboteurs, never as a failure of his own planning.",
