    },
    {
      "keys": ["cowshed", "battle of the cowshed", "fight", "war"],
      "content": "When Mr Jones and a band of men came back to the farm with guns to retake it by force, the animals fought them off in what became known as the Battle of the Cowshed. It was a real victory and a proud day, and it kept the farm free. Snowball led the defence bravely and was wounded by a gunshot — but Napoleon's later account of the battle quietly shrinks Snowball's part in it and enlarges his own. Napoleon will speak of the Battle of the Cowshed gladly, as proof of what the farm can do when it stands together under him.",
